	"working_principles": [
		"Homepage and services hub own the broadest mental health intent.",
		"Broad service categories and more-specific pages own therapy, counseling, and service-specific intent through a faceted parent-context model.",
		"Counseling remains important as a supporting phrase because it still matches several core public labels and GBP-adjacent language.",
		"One commercial page should own one main intent.",
		"Close keyword variants should usually reinforce an existing canonical page instead of becoming a new page.",
		"Contextual parent pages and service-area pages support local relevance and access without duplicating service pages.",
		"Articles should absorb overlapping or informational demand.",
		"Stable commercial pages should remain code-managed and SEO-sensitive.",
		"Do not globally standardize on only therapy or only counseling until keyword research resolves page-level ownership.",
		"A page can have one canonical parent while also linking to secondary service categories, contextual parents, specialties, concern pages, and service areas.",
		"Breadcrumb UI, BreadcrumbList JSON-LD, and visible related-page groups are generated from src/data/page-relationships.ts rather than a route-parser package or Astro-only source of truth.",
		"NocoBase relationship briefs may draft primary-parent rows and related-link buckets, but production rendering remains static and repo-backed."
	],
	"faceted_page_types": [
